tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:23:Deontological reasoning implements deontic logic frameworks to detect conflicts between what entities can/cannot, should/should not, must/must not do or be. The system provides:
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:25:- **Deontic Modalities**: Obligations, permissions, prohibitions, conditionals, exceptions
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:27:- **Conflict Detection**: Identifies contradictions between deontic statements
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:31:## Deontic Modalities
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:33:- **OBLIGATION**: Mandatory requirements (must, shall, required to)
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:34:- **PERMISSION**: Allowed actions (may, can, allowed to)
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:35:- **PROHIBITION**: Forbidden actions (must not, cannot, forbidden to)
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:36:- **CONDITIONAL**: Context-dependent obligations (if/then statements)
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:42:- **PERMISSION_PROHIBITION**: X can do A, X cannot do A
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:43:- **OBLIGATION_PROHIBITION**: X must do A, X must not do A
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:45:- **JURISDICTIONAL**: Conflicts between different legal jurisdictions
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:55:- Multiple modality types and conflict types
tests/gherkin_features/deontological_reasoning_callables/README.md:69:3. Implement fixtures for Background setup
